  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We study the notion of a fundamental group in the framework of descent-exact homological categories. This setting is sufficiently large to include several categories of “algebraic” nature such as almost abelian categories, semi-abelian categories, and categories of topological semi-abelian algebras. For many adjunctions in this context, we describe the fundamental groups by generalised Brown–Ellis–Hopf formulae for the integral homology of groups.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">Elsevier</subfield>
